---
/* Static shell for the "Live now" panel (URS-90…URS-92, URS-103, URS-105).
   Collapsible via <details>/<summary> so it never crowds the bracket stage
   on mobile (URS-92) and is keyboard-operable natively. All dynamic content
   is filled in by src/live/scoreboard.ts at runtime -- this file carries no
   business logic (matches the project's static-chrome convention).

   Starts CLOSED (no `open` attribute): the panel's content height swings
   from a one-line placeholder to potentially many scorecards once the first
   live poll resolves -- if the panel were open by default, that swing pushes
   the bracket stage down after paint, a real cumulative-layout-shift (CLS)
   regression measured against the URS-104/Lighthouse quality bar. Closed by
   default keeps the summary bar's height stable regardless of poll results;
   the "LIVE" badge + "updated Xs ago" stamp in the summary itself signal
   there's something to expand, and expanding is a user-initiated action
   (excluded from CLS as "recent input"). The bracket remains the primary
   element either way (URS-92). */
---

<section id="live-scoreboard" aria-label="Live scores" class="live-scoreboard">
  <details id="live-details">
    <summary class="live-summary">
      <span class="live-title">Live now</span>
      <span id="live-badge" class="ls-badge-header">OFFLINE</span>
      <span id="live-ago" class="live-ago">Connecting…</span>
    </summary>

    <div id="live-cards" class="live-cards" aria-busy="false">
      <p class="ls-empty">Connecting to the live feed…</p>
    </div>

    <p id="live-region" class="sr-only" aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="false"></p>

    <p class="live-credit">
      Live set &amp; game scores via <a href="https://www.espn.com/tennis/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
        >ESPN's public feed</a
      > — unofficial, may lag or differ from official Wimbledon scoring. No point-by-point (0/15/30/40) data
      is available or shown.
    </p>
  </details>
</section>
